{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you consider a native iOS keyboard, it actually applies a bunch of gestures to its keys. Input keys can be pressed and released, while some actions trigger on press. The space bar can by default be long pressed to enter a cursor drag state, while the backspace can be long pressed to repeat the delete backwards operation. Input keys can also be long pressed to show a callout with secondary actions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit comes with keyboard-specific gestures and views that you can use in your own keyboards, to simplify adding and handling gestures to a button."}]},{"anchor":"Keyboard-gestures","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Keyboard gestures"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardGesture"},{"type":"text","text":" enum that defines various gestures:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tap"},{"type":"text","text":" - occurs when a button is pressed then released inside."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"doubleTap"},{"type":"text","text":" - occurs when a button is double tapped."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"press"},{"type":"text","text":" - occurs when a button is pressed down."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"release"},{"type":"text","text":" - occurs when a button is released, inside or outside."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"longPress"},{"type":"text","text":" - occurs when a button is long pressed."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"repeatPress"},{"type":"text","text":" - occurs repeatedly when a button is pressed and held."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit also defines gesture handlers, timers etc. to implement various gestures like repeat presses, space dragging etc."}]},{"anchor":"Binding-gestures-to-a-view","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Binding gestures to a view"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"keyboardGestures"},{"type":"text","text":" view modifier to bind keyboard-specific gestures to any view. This will setup view gestures for a certain action. You can also use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/GestureButton"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/ScrollViewGestureButton"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply complex gestures to a button."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/gestures"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/gestures"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Gestures","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This article describes the KeyboardKit gesture engine and how to use it."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Gestures","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"KeyboardKitPro"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Articles","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/